<DOC><DOCNO> AP880405-0240 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-05-88 0118EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-OilPrices     04-05 0151</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Oil Prices,0157</SECOND><HEAD>Oil Prices Down Slightly in Light Trading</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Oil prices have edged downward in extremelylight trading, which dealers ascribed to a seasonal slowdown, theU.S. holiday weekend and uncertainty over the outcome of an OPECmeeting scheduled later this month.   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the May delivery price ofWest Texas Intermediate, the key U.S. crude, closed down 7 cents at$17.01 per barrel on Monday.   Among refined products, wholesale No. 2 heating oil closed at46.00 cents per gallon, down .15 cent from Thursday's close, andwholesale unleaded gasoline closed at 49.35 cents per gallon, down.03 cent from Thursday.   U.S. commodity markets were closed Friday for the Good Fridayholiday.   Dealers said many market participants were reluctant to buy orsell oil pending the conclusion of an Organization of PetroleumExporting Countries pricing committee meeting April 9 in Vienna.</TEXT></DOC>